'''Epideixis''' is a [[Greek lexicon|Greek term]] referring to a lavish and showey speech. This speech would be typically ornamental and could be argued to be the aim of [[oratory]]. A noted epideixis is performed by [[Gorgias]], an Athenian orator, in [[Plato]]'s [[Gorgias (dialogue)|work]] of the same title.

